libtext-wrapi18n-perl (0.06-8) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Take over for the Debian Perl Group; Closes: #925070 -- RFA/ITA
  * debian/control: Added: Vcs-Git field (source stanza); Vcs-Browser
    field (source stanza); ${misc:Depends} to Depends: field. Changed:
    Homepage field changed to metacpan.org URL; Maintainer set to Debian
    Perl Group <pkg-perl-maintainers@lists.alioth.debian.org> (was:
    Anibal Monsalve Salazar <anibal@debian.org>).
  * Mark package as autopkgtest-able.
  * Drop version from perl build dependency.
  * Switch to source format "3.0 (quilt)".
  * Bump debhelper-compat to 12.
  * Update debian/watch to uscan version 4 and MetaCPAN URL.
  * debian/rules: use dh(1).
  * debian/copyright: use Copyright-Format 1.0.
  * Drop quilt remnants.
  * Remove unneeded debian/dirs.
  * Add DEP3 headers to 01-470250-WrapI18N.pm.patch.
  * Update (build) dependencies.
  * Add /me to Uploaders.
  * Mention module name in long description.
  * Remove trailing whitespace from debian/*.
  * Annotate test-only build dependencies with <!nocheck>.
  * Declare compliance with Debian Policy 4.4.0.

